{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011tmV2sn2riq2uztwng8HWd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both goal conditions are met. TLS is now enabled on the CockroachDB cluster.\n\n## Summary\n\nThe `cockroachdb` cluster (3-node StatefulSet `crdb-cluster`) was converted from insecure to TLS-secured mode:\n\n**1. Certificate generation** (in the `openssl-toolbox` pod):\n- A self-signed **CA** (`ca.crt`/`ca.key`, `CA:true`).\n- A shared **node cert** (`node.crt`, CN=`node`) with SANs covering `localhost`, `127.0.0.1`, all three pod FQDNs, the `crdb-cluster`/`crdb-cluster-public` services, and a wildcard — with EKU `serverAuth,clientAuth`.\n- A **client root cert** (`client.root.crt`, CN=`root`, EKU `clientAuth`).\n\n**2. Delivery** — bundled the certs into the `crdb-certs` Secret.\n\n**3. StatefulSet reconfiguration:**\n- Replaced `--insecure` with `--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs` in the start command.\n- Added an `init-certs` initContainer that copies certs from the read-only secret mount into an `emptyDir` and applies CockroachDB's required permissions (`600` on keys, `644` on certs, `700` dir) — secrets mount too permissively for CockroachDB to accept directly.\n- Switched the liveness/readiness probe scheme to **HTTPS** (secure mode serves the health endpoint over TLS).\n\n**4. Restart** — deleted all 3 pods simultaneously (a mixed secure/insecure cluster can't form quorum, so a rolling one-at-a-time update would deadlock). All 3 came back up `1/1 Running` and re-formed the cluster over TLS.\n\n**Verification:**\n- ✅ Insecure access **rejected**: `ERROR: node is running secure mode, SSL connection required`\n- ✅ Secure access **succeeds**: `SELECT 1;` returns `1`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":310,"cache_creation_input_tokens":778,"cache_read_input_tokens":49006,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":778